{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not a matter of being "viewed as" criminals: under a regime of criminalisation, drug users *are* criminals. {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of drugs will make people aware of their consequences \\(having a prospectus like medicine with known pros and cons - like marijuana for medical usage\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Incarceration](https://beckleyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/paper_07.pdf) of drug offenders is expensive and a burden on taxpayers.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, in the USA, there is a [pharmaceutical opioid crisis](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/us-opioid-epidemic). Drug companies and legal policies cannot be trusted to protect citizens. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Banning drugs is akin to what happens in the film [Minority Report](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minority_Report_\\(film\\)): it's arresting people for what they might do under the influence. {'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Giving up" is preferable to endlessly pursuing an unobtainable goal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This is similar to how legal drugs, such as alcohol, are currently treated in most countries: harmful use is punished and use that does not harm others is not. {'type': 'pro', 'text': "Shooting \\(illegally obtained\\) heroin is like playing Russian roulette every time: if a batch is too strong, over-dosing is likely. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, there were very few production standards \\(if any\\), meaning the consumer did not know what \\(potentially dangerous\\) conditions the alcohol had been manufactured in \\([pg. 4](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Prohibition does not treat addicts, treatment, and prevention of addiction do. Both of these are accomplished far more effectively without the threat of incarceration for merely admitting use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation does not necessarily mean that drugs will be freely available. It is easier to control and regulate drugs when they are legalised as governments can restrict who can make and sell them.'}
